            ">Trump’s first week in office</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-jan-25-1.png" alt="Trump’s first week in office" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><strong>Summary: Trump’s first week of presidency saw him issue many executive orders, which reflected his campaign promises.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Trump’s first week in office was characterized by controversial orders and pardons. He targeted sanctuary cities with <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-new-deportation-policies" target="_blank">new deportation policies</a>, sent thousands of troops to the southern border, and <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-canceled-dei-programs" target="_blank">canceled DEI programs</a> across federal agencies. He also established that his government would recognize <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-only-two-genders" target="_blank">only two genders</a>, male and female. Trump’s pardoning of <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-r1-2-january-6-rioters" target="_blank">January 6 rioters</a> and halting of police reforms have sparked criticism.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">He signed an order to exit the <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-paris-agreement-and-who" target="_blank">Paris Agreement and WHO</a> and declared a national energy emergency. He began reviewing the NAFTA agreement, with plans for renegotiation and sought to establish an External Revenue Service to collect tariffs. He also paused the TikTok ban for 75 days and rolled back many Biden-era sanctions and acts, including the Affordable Care Act, EV bill, and AI safety orders.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">While he has delivered his promise for his conservative base, his promises to address high consumer costs have yet to be fulfilled, particularly in swing states. His push for more energy production as a long-term solution to lower prices hasn’t delivered immediate relief, and tariffs on international trade could further raise costs. While Trump’s administration asserts control, his actions are already fuelling opposition domestically and abroad (<a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-r1-1-orders-and-pardons" target="_blank">Trump-Vance priorities</a>).</p>
        </mj-text> 
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    
