              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">California Fires reignite</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The dangerous wildfires in California picked up again, fueled by strong winds and dry conditions. Multiple fires are burning across the region (<a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-r4-5-map-of-the-wildfire" target="_blank">map of the wildfires</a>). The Hughes fire near Castaic has forced thousands to evacuate, while the Laguna fire and others have sparked evacuations and school closures.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">President Trump plans to visit California and threatens to <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-01-2025-r4-6-withhold-aid" target="_blank">withhold aid</a> unless the state alters water policies. Governor Newsom disputes the claim, stating that Southern California has no water shortage. Rain is expected this weekend, offering some relief to firefighters. However, there is concern that a dry spell afterward could last for weeks, as the Santa Ana wind season can last through March.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
